## Overview

This assignment performs a disparate impact audit of the COMPAS recidivism
risk scoring system using the Broward County cohort (N = 6,172). Building on
the preprocessing pipeline from Assignment 1 and the explainability audit from
Assignment 2, this notebook measures group-level fairness across race and sex
using legally grounded bias metrics.

---

## Tasks

### Task 1: AIR, ME, and SMD
Computes Adverse Impact Ratio (AIR), Marginal Effect (ME), and Standardized
Mean Difference (SMD) for race and sex using both the solas-ai disparity
library and manual implementation. Confirms both methods produce identical
results.

### Task 2: Intersectional Subgroup Analysis
Builds race x sex interaction subgroups and computes AIR for each. Reports
the worst-group AIR and interprets the finding in the context of
intersectionality.

### Task 3: FPR and FNR Disparity
Computes False Positive Rate (FPR) and False Negative Rate (FNR) by race.
Tests the Black vs. White disparity for statistical significance using a
two-proportion z-test.

### Task 4: Publication-Quality Figure
Produces a grouped bar chart of FPR and FNR by race with Caucasian as the
reference group. Saved as error_rate_disparity.png.

### Task 5: Compliance Memo
A 300-word memo addressed to a hypothetical regulator summarizing audit
findings, metrics used, and limitations.

---

## Dependencies

- pandas, numpy, matplotlib, scipy
- statsmodels
- solas-ai (install via: pip install solas-ai)
- scikit-learn, shap, lime, dice-ml (from Assignments 1 and 2)

---

## How to Run

1. Open the notebook in Google Colab
2. Run all cells from top to bottom
3. The Assignment 3 section begins after the Individual Assignment 3 header

